That conclusion was neither wrong as a matter of law nor does it warrant a new trial. The Court has considered all of the arguments of the parties. To the extent not specifically addressed above, they are either moot or without merit. For the reasons explained above, the defendant's motions for judgment as a matter of law pursuant to Rule 50(b) or for a new trial pursuant to Rule 59are denied.
